S-1.name: Head-down Inface Snake
S-1.description: Performers cross the Start Sideline in a head-down inface orientation and remain in head-down inface carving during the entire Pattern. Performers begin by carving towards the Performers' left in the first and third Snake (right in the second Snake). When passing through the centre the first time, each Performer changes to carving towards his/her right in the first and third Snake (left in the second Snake). When passing through the centre the second time, each Performer changes to carving towards his/her left in the first and third Snake (right in the second Snake).
